<h2>UESP Map Help</h2>

<dl>
<dt><strong>How do I use the map?</strong></dt>
	<dd>The map works just like <a href="http://maps.google.com">Google Maps</A> except the game map and locations are displayed instead of Earth's.
	Some common map operations are:
	<ul>
		<li><strong>Zoom In/Out</strong> -- Use the mouse's scroll wheel or the slider control in the upper right corner of the map.</li>
		<li><strong>Pan</strong> -- Use the arrow buttons in the upper left corner of the map or 'drag' the map by left-clicking and dragging the mouse in the map area.
			You can also use the mini overview map in the lower right corner by clicking or dragging the blue map area.</li>
		<li><strong>Center to a Location</strong> -- Double-click the location in the map.</li>
		<li><strong>Reset</strong> -- You can reset the map by clicking in the 'Reset Map' link at the top of the page.</li>
	</ul>

<P>
<dt><strong>How do I find locations?</strong></dt>
	<dd>By default the map shows only certain locations depending on how far you are zoomed in. It will only show all known locations when you are at the highest
		zoom level. You can also search for specific locations by entering the text in the search box at the top-left of the screen and pressing Enter or clicking the
		search button (<img src='images/search-icon.png' alt='[Search Button Image]'/>). Search results will be displayed under the search box if the search results area is open
		(click the <i>"Show Search Results"</i> under the search input box).
	<p />
		You can click on a search result to jump to that location at the current zoom level. Similarly, clicking the "zoom in" icon (<img src="images/zoomicon.gif" alt='[Zoom Button Image]' />)
		can be used to jump to a location at an increased zoom level (one less than the maximum). Click on the <img src="images/iconwikipage.png" alt='[Wiki Page Image]' /> icon to go to the UESP's wiki
		article for that location/
		<p />
		The search results can be cleared by performing a search with no text or by using the 'Reset Search' button (<img src='images/searchreseticon.png' alt='[Reset Search Button Image]' />).</dd>

<P>
<dt><strong>How do I get a permanent link to a location?</strong></dt>
	<dd>Use the <i>"Link to Current Map"</i> in the upper right of the page which will set the page address to the appropriate value. You can then copy the address to
		link to the map later (Right-Click and "Save Link As" in most browsers).</dd>

